Add one more joystick and one more servo, where the second joystick controls only the X-axis movement of Servo 4.

New Setup

Joystick 1 → controls Servo1 (X)(base servo), Servo2 (Y)(left), Servo3 (opposite Y)(right)
Joystick 2 → controls Servo4 (X)(Griper servo)

Your Current Setup
_______________________________________________________________________________________________________________

Joystick1 (controls servo 1, 2, 3)

       * GND → Arduino GND
       * VCC → Arduino 5V
       * VRx → A0 → Servo1 X
       * VRy → A1 → Servo2/3 Y
       * SW → optional digital pin

Joystick2 (controls servo 4 X-axis only)

       * GND → Arduino GND
       * VCC → Arduino 5V
       * VRx → A2 → Servo4 X
       * VRy → leave unconnected or connect to analog pin but ignore in code 
       * SW → optional digital pin



From the project repository, collect the code sketch Transmitter-Code3 and upload it to the transmitter-side Arduino.
From the project repository, collect the code sketch Receiver Code3 and upload it to the Receiver-side Arduino.


